This paper deals with load balancing policies in computer networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also uses Lyapunov-drift analysis, which is a technique commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.IT). The paper also discusses achieving optimal throughput and delay, which are topics related to performance evaluation (cs.PF) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
